**AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML)**

AJAX is a technique used to update parts of a web page without reloading the entire page. It involves making an HTTP request to a server, receiving the response, and then using JavaScript to update the content of the page. Here's how you can use AJAX to replace the contents of a page with the contents of a different URL:

```javascript
// Using jQuery
$.ajax({
  type: 'GET',
  url: 'https://example.com/new-content',
  success: function(data) {
    $('#content-container').html(data);
  }
});

// Using vanilla JavaScript (fetch API)
fetch('https://example.com/new-content')
  .then(response => response.text())
  .then(data => {
    document.getElementById('content-container').innerHTML = data;
  });
```

